incidentsData.title: 7 killed, 3 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli forces fired on an aid convoy and waiting civilians near the Nabulsi roundabout in Gaza City.

incidentsData.title: 12 killed, 50 wounded
incidentsData.description: Shortly after a World Food Programme convoy delivered aid to Gaza City for the first time in several weeks, Israeli quadcopter drones and tanks fired on civilians collecting aid. Sources vary on the number of casualties, from dozens killed to over 50 killed and dozens wounded.

incidentsData.title: 2 killed, 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid on al-Rashid Street in Gaza City. Reports on the number of killed and wounded vary from unknown to as many as five killed.

incidentsData.title: 4 killed
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid on al-Rashid Street in Gaza City.

incidentsData.title: 6 killed, 3 wounded
incidentsData.description: Artillery fire hits people waiting for aid near the Kuwait roundabout in Gaza City. Initial casualty reports said two or three killed and more than 10 wounded. The number killed was later reported as six. We recorded six killed and three wounded.

incidentsData.title: 20 killed, 150 wounded
incidentsData.description: At least 20 civilians killed and more than 150 injured after Israeli forces fired on crowds waiting for aid trucks near the Kuwait roundabout in Gaza City. The Israeli military opened an investigation.

incidentsData.title: International Court of Justice provisional measures order
incidentsData.description: The ICJ orders Israel to "take all measures within its power to prevent" genocide in Gaza, and to "take immediate and effective measures" to enable the delivery of humanitarian aid. The order is part of the case brought by South Africa accusing Israel of committing genocide in Gaza.

incidentsData.title: 2 injured
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. Later reports say three people killed, but it is unclear if they are referring to the same incident.

incidentsData.title: 50 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City.

incidentsData.title: 3 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. Reports say that several are wounded. We recorded three wounded.

incidentsData.title: 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli tanks fired on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. Sources report "a number" of people or injured and many casualties. We recorded two wounded.

incidentsData.title: 13 killed, 2 wouned

incidentsData.title: 2 killed, 6 wounded

incidentsData.title: 2 killed, 2 wounded

incidentsData.title: 5 killed, 3 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli quadcopters shot people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. Source report five killed and several wounded.

incidentsData.title: 4 killed, 24 wounded

incidentsData.title: 3 killed, 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid on al-Rashid St. in Gaza City. Three killed and a number wounded, according to sources. We recorded two wounded.

incidentsData.title: 3 killed
incidentsData.description: Israeli artillery fire hit people waiting for aid on al-Rashid St. in Gaza City. Source report at least three killed.

incidentsData.title: 118 killed, 760 wounded
incidentsData.description: In what became know as "The Flour Massacre", Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Nabulsi Roundabout in Gaza City, killing and wounding at least 878 people.

incidentsData.title: 1 killed, 26 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Nabulsi Roundabout in Gaza City.

incidentsData.title: 1 killed, 10 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli shelling and gunfire hits people waiting for aid at the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. Initial reports of tens or dozens wounded. Later sources say 1 killed, 10 wounded.

incidentsData.title: 1 killed, 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City, in the first of two incidents on the same day in the same location. Source report multiple people wounded. We recorded two.

incidentsData.title: 1 killed, 1 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops again opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. Sources report multiple casualties, but it is unclear how many. We recorded one killed and one wounded.

incidentsData.title: 1 killed, 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli forces prevented 17 World Food Programme aid trucks from entering Gaza City and forced them to unload south of the Netzarim corridor, then fired on civilians who came to collect aid. Sources report one killed an a number wounded. We recorded one killed and two wounded.
incidentsData.sources: al-Rashid St, just south of Netzarim checkpoint

incidentsData.title: 1 killed, 9 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli artillery fire hits people waiting for aid at the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City.

incidentsData.title: 4 killed, 20 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Nabulsi Roundabout in Gaza City. Source report four or five killed and over 20 wounded. We recorded four killed and 20 wounded.

incidentsData.title: 3 killed, 15 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops again opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City.

incidentsData.title: 1 killed, 12 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli tanks and soldiers opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Nabulsi Roundabout in Gaza City. Reports say people were "lured" and "ambushed".

incidentsData.title: 4 killed
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Nabulsi Roundabout in Gaza City. Sources initially report 9 killed and 58 wounded in incidents at both the Nabulsi and Kuwait roundabouts. Later sources say four killed at the Nabulsi Roundabout.

incidentsData.title: 2 killed, 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. Sources initially report 9 killed and 58 wounded in incidents at both the Nabulsi and Kuwait roundabouts. Other source report two killed and a number wounded at the Kuwait Roundabout.

incidentsData.title: 1 killed, 20 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. One killed and at least 20 wounded, according to sources.

incidentsData.title: 1 killed

incidentsData.title: No casualties reported
incidentsData.description: Israeli navy ships off the coast of Gaza fired on people trying to collect aid-dropped aid packages on the beach in northern Gaza. No reports of casualties.

incidentsData.title: No casualties reported
incidentsData.description: Israeli helicopter gunfire hit people waiting for aid at the Kuwait roundabout in Gaza City. No reports of casualties.

incidentsData.title: 5 killed, 24 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. Dozens reported wounded. We recorded 24.

incidentsData.title: No casualties reported
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people trying to collect aid-dropped aid packages in Beit Lahia. No reported casualties.

incidentsData.title: 7 killed, 38 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. The Israeli military denied that troops had attacked people waiting for aid and said the incident was being investigated "with the thoroughness that it deserves". Source say at least 38 wounded.

incidentsData.title: 9 killed, 20 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. More than 20 wounded, according to sources. We recorded 20.

incidentsData.title: 5 killed, 22 wounded
incidentsData.description: An Israeli airstrike hit an UNRWA centre. At least one UNRWA worker was killed, along with four other civilians, and at least 22 were wounded.

incidentsData.title: 6 killed, 83 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City.

incidentsData.title: 10 killed, 24 wounded
incidentsData.description: An Israeli airstrike hit an aid distribution centre in Nuseirat. Casualties included civilians waiting for aid outside. Sources say dozens wounded. We recorded as 24.

incidentsData.title: 20 killed, 155 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli forces, reportedly including troops, tanks, helicopters, and drones fired on people waiting for aid at the Kuwait roundabout, killing at least 20 and wounding more than 155. The Israeli military claimed casualties were caused by Palestinian gunfire and aid trucks hitting people. The following day, troops reportedly fired on people trying to collect bodies of those killed on 14 March.

incidentsData.title: 3 killed
incidentsData.description: Israeli drones fired on people waiting for aid on al-Rashid St., near Gaza City. Some sources report others wounded but are inconclusive.

incidentsData.title: 1 killed, 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. A number wounded, according to sources. We recorded two wounded.

incidentsData.title: 1 killed, 3 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops again opened fire on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. Source report several or a number wounded. We recorded three.

incidentsData.title: 24 killed, 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli airstrike hit people securing an aid convoy and waiting crowds near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. Reports range from 20 to 40 killed and others wounded. We recorded 24 killed and two wounded based on reports from the following day.

incidentsData.title: No casualties reported

incidentsData.title: 23 killed, 23 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli tanks fired on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City.

incidentsData.title: 1 killed, 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops fired on people securing an aid convoy and waiting crowds near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City. Some sources report three killed. We recorded one.

incidentsData.title: 14 killed, 2 wounded

incidentsData.title: 1 killed, 2 wounded

incidentsData.title: 7 wounded

incidentsData.title: 12 killed, 30 wounded

incidentsData.title: 4 killed
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops fired on people waiting for aid near the Kuwait Roundabout in Gaza City.

incidentsData.title: 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli troops fired on people waiting for aid west of Beit Lahia. Multiple people wounded, according to sources. We recorded two.

incidentsData.title: 1 killed, 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli forces fired on an aid convoy shortly after it entered northern Gaza, killing a driver. Artillery hit the area shortly after. In addition to the driver who was killed, sources say a number of people were wounded. We recorded two.

incidentsData.title: No casulaties reported
incidentsData.description: Israeli helicopters fire on people waiting for aid near the beach in northern Gaza, shortly after the American aid pier opened. No casulaties were reported.

incidentsData.title: No casulaties reported
incidentsData.description: Israeli artillery fire lands near people waiting for aid deliveries near the new American aid pier. No casualties were reported.

incidentsData.title: 15 killed

incidentsData.title: 9 killed

incidentsData.title: 8 killed, 12 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli airstrike hits people securing aid delivery at an UNRWA building used to distribute aid, killing at least eight people and injuring 12. Aid committee members and other civilians waiting to receive aid were among those killed and injured.

incidentsData.title: 10 killed, 2 injured
incidentsData.description: Israeli airstrike hits people securing aid delivery and people waiting for aid. Source vary on the number of wounded, from unreported to up to 22. We recorded two wounded.

incidentsData.title: 3 killed, 3 wounded

incidentsData.title: 10 killed

incidentsData.title: 1 wounded

incidentsData.title: 8 killed, 2 wounded

incidentsData.title: 3 killed, 2 wounded

incidentsData.title: 3 wounded

incidentsData.title: 6 killed, 24 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli airstrike hit people outside a bakery in what Israeli authorities had declared the humanitarian zone of al-Mawasi, killing at least six, including two children. Reports say dozens of others were injured. The Israeli military said they were targeting a senior Islamic Jihad militant.

incidentsData.title: Number of casualties unspecified
incidentsData.description: Israeli airstrike hit a water tanker and people collecting water in Jabalia. Sources report an unspecified number of casualties.

incidentsData.title: 8 killed, 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli drone strike hit people collecting water in Rafah. Sources do not specify the number of people injured. We recorded two.

incidentsData.title: 10 killed, 40 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli airstrike hit an UNRWA centre as civilians waited for aid distribution. Sources report at least 40 wounded.

incidentsData.title: 11 killed, 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Two Israeli airstrikes in rapid succession hit a vehicle near a mosque where aid was being distributed, killing civilian aid committee volunteers and people waiting for aid.

incidentsData.title: 6 killed, 2 wounded
incidentsData.description: Israeli forces, reportedly tanks, hit a group of people waiting for aid near a mosque in Gaza City. The same mosque was targeted on 29 October. Sources vary on the number of wounded, from unspecified to dozens. We recorded two.
